# Weather-App-
This is a simple Weather App built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It allows users to check the current weather for any city around the world 🌎 by typing the city name into the search bar 🔍. The app also provides weather details like temperature, humidity, and wind speed 🌬️.

Key Features:

Live Weather Data: Fetches real-time data from the OpenWeather API 🌈.

Search Functionality: Allows users to search for weather based on any city 🌇.

Dynamic Search Suggestions: As the user types, suggestions for popular cities are shown 🏙️.

Weather Information: Displays temperature 🌡️, humidity 💧, and wind speed 🌬️.

Beautiful UI: Simple and clean interface with icons for weather data 🌞.

🛠️ Technologies Used:
HTML5: For the basic structure of the webpage 🏗️.

CSS3: For styling the page and making it visually appealing 🎨.

JavaScript: For fetching live weather data and creating interactive search functionality 💻.

OpenWeather API: For accessing current weather information 🌤️.

📸 Features:
1. Weather Info
When a user enters a city name and clicks the search button, the app fetches the weather details and displays:

Temperature in Celsius (°C) 🌡️

Humidity as a percentage (%) 💧

Wind Speed in km/h 🌬️


🚀 How to Use:
1. Clone the Repository:
Clone this project to your local machine by running the following command:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/weather-app.git
2. Open the App:
Navigate to the project folder:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd weather-app
Open the index.html file in your browser 🌐.

3. Search Weather:
Start typing the name of any city (e.g., "London" or "New York") 🔍.

Click the search icon 🖱️ to fetch the weather details.

